I cannot believe anyone considers this a "great recipe." All that mayo and sour cream...I feel nauseous just thinking about it. For anyone who actually cares about their health (and weight) try German potato salad - a much tastier alternative, and you can actually taste the potatoes!

Rating: 3
This has been "my" potato salad recipe since I tried it. I too use a little less mayo and cream, and add an extra egg (or garnish it with deviled eggs), and I like lots of mustard. For even better texture and flavor, I recommend Julia Child's foolproof system: Scoop out some potato-cooking water before draining the potatoes. Drain the water out of the pan, cover and let the potatoes firm up in the hot pan for 3-4 minutes. Turn out into a bowl and toss with the vinegar and a few spoonfuls of the cooking water. The potatoes will absorb the liquid as they cool and with the extra moistness they won't soak up so much dressing.

