Rating: 3
Make this for friends at a bar-b-que (along with Triple-Bean Bake. I boiled the potatoes first with skins, then cut into 1" pieces, saving as much skin as possible. I followed advice of others and also used reduced fat mayo, and reduced the sour cream amt to 1/2 c. I also added about 1/2 c. or so of diced red bell pepper for color. That addition was perfect for color and mild flavor. I increased the eggs from 2 to 4---a must! The suggestion to add crisp, crumbled bacon just before serving is a real plus for both presentation and flavor! I made this dish up the day before but would not do it quite that soon next time. I would, instead, make it the night before. It got just a little bit watery at the bottom for me. I will definitely make it again. Everyone asked for the recipe.

