Rating: 3
This brought positive reviews at a Father's Day BBQ. It is a tasty and healthy basic recipe from which I expanded and experimented - both modifying and adding a few ingredients. My modifications: - leave the skins on the potatoes (adds interest, nutrients and convenience) - use 4 eggs instead of 2 - use 1/2 cup fat-free sour cream - use low-fat mayo My extra yummies added for crunch and flavor: - crisp snow peas - radishes - mustard powder - horseradish - orange cherry tomatoes - carrots - sunflower seed sprouts - celery seed Bon appetit!

