Rating: 3
This would be a "2 forks" without significant modifications... I eliminated the white wine vinegar altogher (didn't have any), but I might add it to the dressing and only use about 1.5 tsp. I also decreased the mayo to 1/2 cup, replaced onion w/shallots, and, most importantly, used a mix of GRAINY + HONEY Dijon. If I didn't have the Honey Dijon, I would have added regular honey to offset Dijon's inherent bitterness, without sacrificing its pungent flavor. The Grainy Dijon adds a nice texture and looks more interesting for serving. Maybe using green onions, or adding radishes, etc. to this average potato salad will make it a winner!

